{% set prompt %}You are given the first row of a CSV file. Your task is to decide whether this row represents column headers or actual data.

When deciding, consider factors such as:
	•	Whether the values look like descriptive column names (e.g., “name”, “age”, “email”, “price”).
	•	Whether the values appear to be actual data entries (e.g., numbers, dates, full names).
	•	Whether the row contains mixed data types that are unlikely for headers.
	•	Whether the row contains special characters or formatting typical of data rather than headers.

First row:
{{row}}{% endset %}

